Various messages have been circulating on social media suggesting that private security guards had planned to close malls and threatened violence against certain groups of the population. JOHANNESBURG -  Private Security Industry Regulatory Authority (PSiRA) has reiterated there is no plan for a protest by any of its members on Thursday. Various messages have been circulating on social media suggesting that private security guards had planned to close malls and threatened violence against certain groups of the population. PSiRA CEO Manabela Chauke said: “We want to appeal to anybody who is continuing to distribute those messages to stop doing so. We assure the nation that we will be getting to the bottom of this distribution and we will be prosecuting the person who originated the first message.”